<exercise id="fs-idp286976176">
<problem id="fs-idp65459664">
<para xmlns:data="http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/dom.html#custom-data-attribute" id="fs-idp56590528">For each of the following pairs of ions, write the formula of the compound they will form:</para><para id="fs-idp101562960">(a) K<sup>+</sup>, O<sup>2−</sup></para>
<para id="fs-idp236810896">(b) <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>NH</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>+</m:mo></m:msup><m:mtext>,</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>PO</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>3−</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idp62582192">(c) Al<sup>3+</sup>, O<sup>2−</sup></para>
<para id="fs-idp19798176">(d) Na<sup>+</sup>, <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>CO</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>2−</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-idp143769280">(e) Ba<sup>2+</sup>, <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>PO</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>3−</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></para>
